InverseKinematics
Interface for inverse kinematics computations.
InverseKinematicsCrane
The inverse kinematics for a simple arm with a servo and two linear motors: a stand servo to set the direction to target (0°: y-direction), femur and and tibia linear motor to position the gripper in the directed plane.
InverseKinematicsIterative
Inverse kinematics computations based on iterative approximation (downhill approach).
InverseKinematicsIterativeWithStandServo
Inverse kinematics computations based on iterative approximation (downhill approach).
InverseKinematicsJacobian
Inverse kinematics computations based on the Jacobian matrix.
InverseKinematicsSimpleArm
The inverse kinematics for a simple arm with three servos: a stand servo to set the direction to target (0°: y-direction), femur and tibia servo to position the gripper in the directed plane.
InverseKinematicsSimpleArm2
The inverse kinematics for a simple arm with one servo and two linear motors that construct servo-like joints: a stand servo to set the direction to target (0°: y-direction), femur and tibia linear motors generate joint angles to position the gripper in the directed plane.
InverseKinematicsSimpleArmLinear
The inverse kinematics for a simple arm with three servos: a stand servo to set the direction to target (0°: y-direction), femur servo and tibia linear motor to position the gripper in the directed plane.
InversePosFunction
A function to be minimized for inverse kinematics computation to reach a certain component position with the help of servo angles and linear motor lengths.
